CMPG638 Project II Instructions

There are two scripts for ProjectII: tags.py and conceptID.py

1.	The first will find all active concepts with specified tag, and compare a given term to the list of FSN’s for those active tagged concepts
2.	The second will create a list of all active FSN’s and ask you to enter a concept id to compare to the whole list

The first script, tags.py, will ask the user to enter the tag for concepts you want, e.g., “(disorder)”.
It will then ask you to enter a term to compare to that list and will first compare all terms according to their cosine distance.
This list will be sorted in descending order so the higher scores at the top of the list represent more similar terms.
It will then take the top 10 elements and run them through the PubMed and CODER Bert models to get the semantic similarity.

The conceptsID.py script is very similar to the first.
The only difference is that the user will be asked to enter a concept id and the program will retrieve the specified term for that id.
It will then compare that term to all active FSN’s just like the above.

*Two models were used for semantic similarity because it appears that PubMed Bert consistently gives very high scores that may not always be accurate.
Thus, I added another model to provide more accurate similarities by providing different weights for each score.
PubMed has a 60% weight on the total and CODER has a 40% weight.

